SNAPSHOTS

sudo pacman -S snapper

then

sudo snapper -c root create --description "just-in-case"

should things fuck up

sudo snapper list (find id)

sudo snapper rollback "insert_id_here"

FIREWALL

sudo pacman -S ufw

then

sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow ssh

AUR

sudo pacman -S --needed base-devel git

then

git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/yay.git

then

cd yay

then

makepkg -si

XLIBRE (if on artix you don't have to do this, it should already be in your package manager.)

nano /etc/pacman.conf

add

# XLIBRE
[xlibre]
Server = https://x11libre.net/repo/arch_based/x86_64

then

sudo pacman -Syu (ensures xlibre server is added to your packages, then replaces xorg/x11 stuff with xlibre.)

